    "Three synthetic data sets have been built for object tracking: VIsual PERception (VIPER) (Richter et al. 2017), Virtu-alKITTI2 (Cabon et al. 2020) and SHIFT (Sun et al. 2022); and four for pedestrian tracking: Virtual Person Tracking Benchmark #1 (VirtualPTB1) (Kerim et al. 2021a), Person Tracking of Synthetic sequences (PTAW217Synth) (Kerim et al. 2021b), Joint Track Auto (JTA) (Fabbri et al. 2018) and MOTSynth (Fabbri et al. 2021).",
